</span><span style="color: rgb(230, 0, 0); font-weight: lighter;">Yes, on closing, colors will be restored, but it can lead to some problems -&gt; if the game will crash or a fatal error will be raised, all previous colors will not going to be restored.</span></p></blockquote><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h3 style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; color: rgb(206, 206, 206); font-family: &quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;, monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;">	3. Figures generation</h3><p style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; color: rgb(206, 206, 206); font-family: &quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;, monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"></p><p style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; color: rgb(206, 206, 206); font-family: &quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;, monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;">	Let''s check how figures are generated inside the main cycle. We have stored data from our prepared scene in which for each figure there are point positions, the number of polygons, vertex indexes per polygon, and the number of vertexes per polygon. All this data basically will be passed to the init function of an MFnMesh object, which will create our polygons. Single figure generation:</p><p style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; color: rgb(206, 206, 206); font-family: &quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;, monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"></p><pre class="ql-syntax" spellcheck="false" style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px; padding: 5px 10px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; background-color: rgb(35, 36, 31); border-radius: 3px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: rgb(248, 248, 242); overflow: visible;"><span class="hljs-keyword" style="box-sizing: border-box;">def</span> <span class="hljs-title function_" style="box-sizing: border-box;">create_figures</span>(<span class="hljs-params" style="box-sizing: border-box;">self, figures_creation_data, parent</span>):

