e will be able later simply to rotate our figure in a given direction. </p><p style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; color: rgb(206, 206, 206); font-family: &quot;JetBrains Mono&quot;, monospace; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br style="box-sizing: border-box;"></p><pre class="ql-syntax" spellcheck="false" style="cursor: text; box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px; padding: 5px 10px; counter-reset: list-1 0 list-2 0 list-3 0 list-4 0 list-5 0 list-6 0 list-7 0 list-8 0 list-9 0; background-color: rgb(35, 36, 31); border-radius: 3px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: rgb(248, 248, 242); overflow: visible;"><span class="hljs-keyword" style="box-sizing: border-box;">def</span> <span class="hljs-title function_" style="box-sizing: border-box;">generate_random_figure</span>(<span class="hljs-params" style="box-sizing: border-box;">self</span>):

